Validation and Test Plan 
Testing Methods
-Unit Testing: Check whether each module works correctly.
-Integration Testing: Test how different modules interact with each other.
-System Testing: Verify that the whole system works according to user scenarios.
-Usability Testing: Evaluate whether students can easily use the interface.
Validation
-Test the system using realistic user scenarios.
-Check if email and SMS notifications are sent correctly.
-Verify that courses and assignments can be added to the planner without errors.
Performance Evaluation
-Measure response time and overall system performance.
-Check accuracy and possible error rates.
-Review security and data privacy protections.
Success Criteria
-Users receive notifications on time.
-The system runs without crashes or data loss during normal use.
-Users can organize their courses and tasks successfully.
Security and privacy measures are properly implemented.
